.TH "gfs2_get_link" 9 "gfs2_get_link" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
gfs2_get_link \- Follow a symbolic link
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "const char *" gfs2_get_link
.BI "(struct dentry *dentry "  ","
.BI "struct inode *inode "  ","
.BI "struct delayed_call *done "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dentry" 12
The dentry of the link
.IP "inode" 12
The inode of the link
.IP "done" 12
destructor for return value
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This can handle symlinks of any size.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success or error code
